Reverse of a number
Send Feedback
Write a program to generate the reverse of a given number N. Print the corresponding reverse number.
Note : If a number has trailing zeros, then its reverse will not include them. For e.g., reverse of 10400 will be 401 instead of 00401.


Input format :
Integer N
Output format :
Corresponding reverse number
Constraints:
0 <= N < 10^8
Sample Input 1 :
1234
Sample Output 1 :
4321
Sample Input 2 :
1980
Sample Output 2 :
891


#include<iostream>
using namespace std;

int main() {
	// Write your code here
	int n;
	cin >> n;
	int rev = 0;
	int ldigit = n;
	while(ldigit !=0){
		int r = ldigit %10;
		rev = rev*10 + 	r;
		ldigit = ldigit / 10;
	}
	cout << rev;
}
